description: One song has ruled the pop chart for over a month. One album has topped the album chart for two months. But there are signs this week that both could face serious challengers soon.
title: Taylor Swift and Post Malone top the charts again. How long can their dominance last?

description: The jazz saxophonist talks about creating a "dance" record, plus Washington performs live for World Cafe.
title: Kamasi Washington on his latest album 'Fearless Movement'

description: Code Switch co-host B.A. Parker on what to do with the debris of Southern sins as we celebrate Juneteenth.
title: Appreciating our enslaved ancestors despite the relics of the Confederacy

description: After a stroke left Howard Blatt unable to speak, he helped create a support group for other people with aphasia, a brain condition that impairs communication. He recently died at age 88.
title: Howard Blatt, stroke survivor who co-founded an aphasia support group, died at 88

description: Problems caused by the attack included delayed or lost lab results, medication errors, and an absence of routine safety checks to prevent potentially fatal mistakes, doctors and nurses told reporters.
title: Cyberattack led to harrowing lapses at Ascension hospitals, clinicians say

description: The office of New Mexico Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham confirmed at least one death as the state of emergency covers the village of Ruidoso and neighboring tribal lands.
title: New Mexico governor declares emergency as thousands flee wildfire

description: Willie Mays is widely considered to be the greatest baseball player of all time. The 'Say Hey Kid' had incomparable skills and an infectious smile. He dazzled on the field and off.
title: Willie Mays - the 'Say Hey Kid' considered baseball's best all-around player - dies at 93
